The Nigeria House of Representatives has asked the National Communication Commission to extend the deadline for Nigerian Identification Number. The extension is expected to last for 10 weeks, ending 28 February 2021 to give enough room for all citizens to register The extension will also help to give Telecommunication companies enough time to register their customers Rep. @ndudi04 moved a motion on the urgent need to call on the Nigerian Communication Commission @NgComCommission to increase the 2weeks deadline for the implementation of the new sim card registration rules and it was seconded by Rep. Francis. pic.twitter.com/3aWQHGnDdo â€” House of Reps NGR (@HouseNGR) December 16, 2020